    <briefdescription>
<para>Recursive mutex templated on a backend policy. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>When Backend = <ref refid="structNullMutexBackend" kindref="compound">NullMutexBackend</ref>, the entire class compiles to nothing (1-byte handle member, all methods are no-ops). When a real RTOS backend is injected, this provides thread-safe recursive locking.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>Backend</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Static policy class satisfying the <ref refid="structNullMutexBackend" kindref="compound">NullMutexBackend</ref> contract. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
